casebody.data:
Mildred NOLAND, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 8702. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Nov. 29, 1938. Raine Ewell, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Frank J. Hennessy, U. S. Atty., and S. P. Murman, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of San Francisco, Cal.

Before DENMAN, MATHEWS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of-dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
